H3.text: In which 1956 film did actress Gina Lollobrigida make her debut in American films. Trapese

A4.text: She played the principal female lead in the circus drama Trapeze (1956) directed by Carol Reed and co-starring with Burt Lancaster and Tony Curtis.

A5.text: Her performance in The World's Most Beautiful Woman (also known as Beautiful But Dangerous, 1955) led to her receiving the first David di Donatello Award for Best Actress.
